v0.1.description:
We finally have our first release for the game client, along with some much needed changes to the APWorld.
All instructions for setup can be found in the repo's [README](https://github.com/Scrungip/FNaFBAP/blob/main/README.md).

If you have issues, please contact me on Discord. My username is scrungip
v0.1.title: Five Nights at Fuckboy's Archipelago Integration ALPHA Release

v0.1.1.description:
Updates:
- APWorld properly removes Godly weapons if Interior Walls is not on
- APWorld removes most unnecessary items based on settings, this helps open up space for filler and fixes issues with other games.

- Game client has been updated and things that weren't working before should be now
v0.1.1.title: ALPHA Hotfix

v0.2.description:
# Changes from previous release
APWorld:
- Added Levelsanity
- Adjusted combat logic
- Fixed Interior Walls logic

Game Client:
- Added Interior Walls support
- Added Levelsanity support
- Adjusted Trade Quest item drop rates
- The Puppet no longer has a timer, and is instead fought by interacting with it in the Restrooms.
- Made Interior Walls hopefully slightly less painful to navigate.


Realistically this should be the last update for a little while unless I need to fix something, I've gotten pretty much everything I wanted in.

v1.0.0.description:
This release should stand as the final big release for Fuckboy's 1, since I can't really think of anything I want to add to it anymore, aside from some small things that may come later down the line.
Here's the patch notes (or at least what I can remember...)

# Changes from 0.4.0
- Bonnie's "Guitar Smash" has been replaced with the new "Guitar Riff" move, which attacks the entire group instead of one enemy and does not remove your guitar
- A goal option has been added, you can now choose to fight Puppetmaster BB as your final boss should you choose to do so
- There's a new option that adds checks relating to my self insert, because I thought it was silly
- Added an inventory item that *should* allow you to change the room port on your save file, though this remains untested
- Fixed oddity when starting a new game after having already loaded a save file
- Fixed the AP client hanging when other games have specific unicode characters in their name
- Fixed Pirate's Cove Camera respawning after being defeated
- Fixed generation errors relating to turning off too many options
- Fixed incorrect Random Starter behavior
- Renamed the Trade Quest checks, because they in fact are on the Show Stage and *not* in the Dining Area
- Proper compatibility with AP versions 0.6.2 and higher.
- Added an archipelago.json file, which will be necessary once Archipelago 0.7.0 comes out.

I did more testing than I typically do with these updates this time so *hopefully* nothing breaks catastrophically but we'll see.
v1.0.0.title: Five Nights at Fuckboy's AP - The "I really need to finish this update" Update
